For someone who is so fascinated by old papers, the support from the National Trust and Arts Council England and the possibility to stay at the castle almost four months as a dream. (To be honest, I have extended my stay a little.)
Rhodes spent time exploring the Victorian "new" castle, going through archives and studying many treasures and curiosities, such as the head of hyenas on the wall and bottles that have been dumped for centuries in the ditch.
